My CSV Dictionary¶

my_csv2dict.read_csv(product_name=<type 'str'>, directory=u'C:\\Users\\KILKISZenbook\\Documents\\Python\\KBE\\components\\payload\\database\\eoir')[source]¶

my_csv2dict.py is a file containing the function read_csv which allows the user to quickly call a directory within the project folder, also for convenience the packages os and sys are imported when directories.py is imported with the * specifier. Finally the dictionary DIRS contains common directories so as to avoid multiple calls to get_dir. Finally since the entries in DIRS are outputs of get_dir the inherent directory checking is also present. Thus an invalid directory will raise errors.

Parameters:path (str) – This is the path to the filename.
